06ae92f0-524c-4ec1-b73c-02b2094c4b82.do_description: To make the output, you have to...count the grey grid and place the meeting point of the colored grid-down through with the same count.
06ae92f0-524c-4ec1-b73c-02b2094c4b82.grid_description: The output grid size...same as the input grid. copy the input grid without the grey grid.
06ae92f0-524c-4ec1-b73c-02b2094c4b82.see_description: In the input, you should see...the number of grey grid and the meeting point of the colored grid.

3ca79cdd-0c3f-4781-beeb-a0b27ba0ec85.do_description: To make the output, you have to....different color
3ca79cdd-0c3f-4781-beeb-a0b27ba0ec85.see_description: In the input, you should see...green

8e745458-2b43-4f9a-b5f2-b90d11655dd7.do_description: To make the output, you have to...count how many gray blocks there are. Move the row of horizontally blocks down however many spaces there are to match the number of gray blocks.
8e745458-2b43-4f9a-b5f2-b90d11655dd7.grid_description: The output grid size...will remain the same size as the input grid.
8e745458-2b43-4f9a-b5f2-b90d11655dd7.see_description: In the input, you should see...a row of blocks filling the grid vertically and horizontally. You will also see a set of gray blocks.

e148e902-b813-4229-9015-9b5a5f20135f.do_description: To make the output, you have to...move the horizontal line down the same number of lines as there are grey boxes, then fill in the boxes with black
e148e902-b813-4229-9015-9b5a5f20135f.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same
e148e902-b813-4229-9015-9b5a5f20135f.see_description: In the input, you should see...two intersecting lines and a number of grey boxes

f9b8d27e-544a-420a-992b-927ece0ddd75.do_description: To make the output, you have to... First, copy the input grid but make the background all black, with no grey grid.  Then, count the grey grid at the top right corner in the input grid. Next, move the horizontal line down according to the number of the grey grid and move the vertical line according to the number of the grey grid and draw it on the output grid (for example, if the grey grid is 1, then move the lines down or to the left by 1 grid)
f9b8d27e-544a-420a-992b-927ece0ddd75.grid_description: The output grid size... is the same as the input grid
f9b8d27e-544a-420a-992b-927ece0ddd75.see_description: In the input, you should see...  colored horizontal and vertical lines on a black background. And grey grid at the top right corner, which indicate how many grid you need to move your horizontal and vertical lines.
